<p>I made the bottom and top radiuses and the height <a  href="https://digitalfire.com/picture/2550">parametric</a>. I made the diameter of the pouring ring = top diameter of the pot + 2 mm. The walls are 2mm thick because my <a  href="https://digitalfire.com/glossary/3d+printer">3D printer</a> prints <a  href="https://digitalfire.com/glossary/0.8mm+thickness">0.4mm</a> wide (that means two passes for each layer).</p>
